history.p: Nielsen's first opus-numbered work was composed while he was studying composition with Orla Rosenhoff. In 1888, the Suite had its first performance in Tivoli where Andante tranquillo e Scherzo (CNW 31) had been premiered the previous year. The following year Nielsen revised the final movement; the revised version was performed for the first time at a concert in Tivoli in May 1889.
